Dialogue: 0,0:00:08.47,0:00:15.08,OP,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,I want to shine on you,\Nand always like that dazzling sun.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:15.38,0:00:18.75,OP,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,I will defend you\Nfrom all the darkness.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:18.85,0:00:24.75,OP,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,This is the truth from my heart.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:25.76,0:00:39.54,OP,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,If only our hearts could connect,\NI could get you to believe me.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:39.64,0:00:46.31,OP,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Even if you can't\Nsee it now, don't lose it.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:46.48,0:00:54.25,OP,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Your kindness won't be in vain.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:55.08,0:01:01.66,OP,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,You'll be carried aloft by the wind\Nto somewhere that isn't here.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:02.06,0:01:08.77,OP,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,You'll cross the sea and cross time,\Nand I know you'll blossom one day.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:08.93,0:01:15.41,OP,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Whatever the day,\NI'll be there for you.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:15.84,0:01:22.05,OP,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,I hope I can watch over you\Nlike the sun for all time.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:22.05,0:01:32.02,OP,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,This is the truth from my heart.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:38.13,0:01:45.60,Dialogue,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,To tell you about Jiguro, I should start\Nby telling you about my childhood.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:49.17,0:01:54.41,Dialogue,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Unlike Yogo, Kanbal has no fields\Nthat produce bountiful harvests.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:55.38,0:01:59.72,Dialogue,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,All it has are steep mountains\Nand rocky grasslands.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:00.48,0:02:02.92,Dialogue,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,The people make a living\Nby tilling the poor soil...
Dialogue: 0,0:02:02.92,0:02:05.66,Dialogue,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,...eking out what little grain\Nand potatoes they can from it...
Dialogue: 0,0:02:05.66,0:02:08.16,Dialogue,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,...and by grazing Kanbal goats.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:09.16,0:02:12.76,Dialogue,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,That's the kind of place\NI was born and raised in.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:13.53,0:02:18.53,Signs,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Episode 21\NJiguro Musa
Dialogue: 0,0:02:19.70,0:02:24.07,Dialogue,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,My father, Karna Yonsa, was the\Nroyal family's personal physician.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:24.71,0:02:30.18,Dialogue,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,My mother died when I was five,\Nbut thanks to my father...
Dialogue: 0,0:02:30.18,0:02:34.85,Dialogue,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,...I led a happy life,\Nnever wanting for anything.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:36.75,0:02:41.16,Dialogue,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,I was too young to realize it,\Nbut by that point...
Dialogue: 0,0:02:41.79,0:02:46.56,Dialogue,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,...my father was already caught up\Nin a situation he couldn't get out of.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:48.87,0:02:51.27,Dialogue,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,My father, chief physician\Nto the king of Kanbal...
Dialogue: 0,0:02:51.27,0:02:53.94,Dialogue,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,...had been ordered to\Npoison the king by Logsam...
Dialogue: 0,0:02:53.94,0:02:57.14,Dialogue,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,...the king's younger brother,\Nwho had his eyes on the throne.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:57.14,0:03:00.78,Dialogue,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Logsam had threatened to\Nkill his daughter if he refused.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:01.28,0:03:04.48,Dialogue,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,And so my father had\Nno choice but to agree.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:05.28,0:03:10.59,Dialogue,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,However, he knew that as soon as\Nhe'd succeeded in poisoning the king...
Dialogue: 0,0:03:10.59,0:03:14.06,Dialogue,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,...his and his daughter's lives would\Nbe forfeit because of what he knew.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:38.48,0:03:42.65,Dialogue,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Caught up in Logsam's machinations,\Nmy father found himself isolated.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:43.12,0:03:47.86,Dialogue,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,But he had one friend in the palace\Nthat he trusted implicitly.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:49.23,0:03:51.03,Dialogue,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,That man was Jiguro.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:53.50,0:03:56.40,Dialogue,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Jiguro was a member\Nof the King's Spears...
Dialogue: 0,0:03:56.40,0:03:59.07,Dialogue,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,...a group of nine men\Nwho served the king.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:00.50,0:04:06.88,Dialogue,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,The King's Spears was\Ncomprised of elite spear-wielders...
Dialogue: 0,0:04:06.88,0:04:10.11,Dialogue,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,...the leaders of Kanbal's\Nnine ethnic tribes.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:10.38,0:04:14.95,Dialogue,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Jiguro was the youngest man ever\Nto be elected to the King's Spears...
Dialogue: 0,0:04:14.95,0:04:17.99,Dialogue,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,...and was lauded as\NKanbal's most powerful hero.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:19.16,0:04:24.79,Dialogue,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Although my father regretted\Ninvolving his friend in this terrible plot...
Dialogue: 0,0:04:24.79,0:04:29.07,Dialogue,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,...he resolved to reveal\NLogsam's plot to Jiguro.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:29.50,0:04:35.07,Dialogue,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,In a matter of days, I will administer\Nthe final dose of poison to the king.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:35.51,0:04:40.54,Dialogue,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Once the king is dead,\NI will inevitably be punished.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:41.84,0:04:45.08,Dialogue,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,But my daughter is\Ncompletely innocent.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:45.28,0:04:48.48,Dialogue,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,You are the only one I can turn to.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:49.02,0:04:51.02,Dialogue,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,I realize that I'm asking you\Nto do the impossible.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:51.02,0:04:56.73,Dialogue,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Ever since my wife passed away, though,\NBalsa has been my entire world.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:58.16,0:05:00.93,Dialogue,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,I beg you, take my daughter\Nand flee the country.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:13.08,0:05:16.55,Dialogue,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Apparently, Jiguro refused\Nmy father's request.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:17.88,0:05:19.35,Dialogue,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,It's no wonder.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:20.82,0:05:24.42,Dialogue,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Even though the request came\Nfrom Jiguro's close friend...
Dialogue: 0,0:05:24.42,0:05:29.76,Dialogue,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,...to accept would mean forfeiting\Nnot only his status and honor...
Dialogue: 0,0:05:29.76,0:05:32.40,Dialogue,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,...but it would also\Nspell his own doom.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:56.92,0:06:01.16,Dialogue,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,In the evening of that same day,\Npalace soldiers came to our home.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:02.59,0:06:07.20,Dialogue,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Logsam must have already figured\Nout what my father was planning.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:20.91,0:06:25.98,Dialogue,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,I'm here at the request of your father.\NCome with me right now.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:26.78,0:06:30.22,Dialogue,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Although he had initially\Nrefused my father...
Dialogue: 0,0:06:30.22,0:06:34.69,Dialogue,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,...for some reason, he said these words,\Ntook my hesitant hand in his...
Dialogue: 0,0:06:34.69,0:06:36.89,Dialogue,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,...and we left our\Nhomeland of Kanbal.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:54.44,0:06:56.88,Dialogue,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Jiguro...forgive me...
Dialogue: 0,0:07:07.16,0:07:10.93,Dialogue,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,If Jiguro hadn't come\Nfor me when he did...
Dialogue: 0,0:07:11.29,0:07:14.33,Dialogue,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,...I'm certain that I would\Nhave been killed that day.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:15.67,0:07:21.14,Dialogue,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,We then spent an entire day traversing\Nthe long caves along the Kanbal border...
Dialogue: 0,0:07:21.60,0:07:24.94,Dialogue,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,...eventually crossing into the\Nterritory of the Shin-Yogo empire.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:26.11,0:07:31.01,Dialogue,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,I was completely exhausted,\Nbut I couldn't sleep at all that night.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:31.71,0:07:34.82,Dialogue,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,For one thing, Jiguro hadn't\Nexplained anything to me...
Dialogue: 0,0:07:34.82,0:07:37.92,Dialogue,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,...and his tension was contagious.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:38.92,0:07:42.73,Dialogue,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Jiguro was on his guard,\Nalert for approaching pursuers.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:51.10,0:07:56.17,Dialogue,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Five days after we began our flight,\Nour first pursuer found us.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:56.94,0:08:00.01,Dialogue,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,The man who appeared\Nwas one of the King's Spears.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:04.05,0:08:07.92,Dialogue,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,At first, I had no idea that the\Nman was there to hunt us down.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:08.52,0:08:11.55,Dialogue,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,After all, the two of them\Nwere speaking so calmly.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:13.46,0:08:16.86,Dialogue,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Was it Logsam who\Nsent you after us?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:19.23,0:08:22.30,Dialogue,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Logsam is an even worse\Ntyrant than I imagined.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:22.60,0:08:23.77,Dialogue,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,That's true.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:24.17,0:08:29.01,Dialogue,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,But this has given me the chance to\Nfulfil a dream that I've had for years.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:29.41,0:08:32.68,Dialogue,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,I've always felt a\Nsense of dissatisfaction...
Dialogue: 0,0:08:32.68,0:08:35.48,Dialogue,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,...over the fact that I haven't\Nhad a chance to challenge you...
Dialogue: 0,0:08:35.48,0:08:38.98,Dialogue,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,...ever since you achieved the\Ntop rank in the King's Spears.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:39.45,0:08:42.32,Dialogue,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,I also have to question\Nif it's truly necessary...
Dialogue: 0,0:08:42.32,0:08:45.52,Dialogue,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,...for a spear dance to be\Npart of a life-or-death struggle.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:45.76,0:08:46.96,Dialogue,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,You do, do you?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:50.33,0:08:53.26,Dialogue,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Perhaps it's because I had\Nthose very same feelings...
Dialogue: 0,0:08:53.26,0:08:56.00,Dialogue,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,...that I find myself\Nstanding here right now.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:00.50,0:09:03.81,Dialogue,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,What are you doing?\NAre you mocking me?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:04.21,0:09:08.28,Dialogue,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,No. This is a genuine\Nfight to the death.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:32.97,0:09:34.00,Dialogue,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,I'm sorry.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:34.94,0:09:37.44,Dialogue,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,I can never return to Kanbal.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:38.61,0:09:41.54,Dialogue,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,And so I can't bring you\Nback to our homeland.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:50.35,0:09:51.42,Dialogue,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Let's go.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:57.29,0:10:02.47,Dialogue,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,It was obvious that Jiguro had\Nnot tried to avoid fighting that man.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:03.13,0:10:05.60,Dialogue,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,To this day,\NI still don't understand why.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:05.60,0:10:08.50,Dialogue,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,But since he had reached\Nthe top at such a young age...
Dialogue: 0,0:10:08.50,0:10:13.44,Dialogue,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,...maybe he wanted, just once,\Nto see what he was really capable of.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:14.34,0:10:18.98,Dialogue,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,That might have just been\Nwishful thinking on my part...
Dialogue: 0,0:10:18.98,0:10:22.42,Dialogue,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,...wanting to believe that the\Nbrief fight had nothing to do with me.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:23.42,0:10:27.39,Dialogue,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,At the same time,\Nthough, it struck me...
Dialogue: 0,0:10:27.39,0:10:32.13,Dialogue,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,...that my situation was even\Nmore dire than I ever imagined.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:32.83,0:10:38.17,Dialogue,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,I realized that my only hope of\Nsurvival was to go with this man.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:39.07,0:10:42.40,Dialogue,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,After that encounter,\Nwe entered a city in Yogo...
Dialogue: 0,0:10:42.77,0:10:46.71,Dialogue,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,...to get a replacement spearhead\Nfor Jiguro's broken spear.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:51.85,0:10:55.35,Dialogue,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,That swordsmith was\Nstubborn even back then.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:55.68,0:10:58.75,Dialogue,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,At first, he refused to take the job.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:00.82,0:11:05.83,Dialogue,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,If at all possible, I'd like\Nto avoid killing anyone else...
Dialogue: 0,0:11:05.83,0:11:09.17,Dialogue,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,...but I have no idea what\Nthat number may even be.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:10.57,0:11:15.30,Dialogue,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,As I know you have the skills to do so,\NI would like you to forge me a spear...
Dialogue: 0,0:11:15.30,0:11:17.47,Dialogue,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,...that is equal to any Yogo sword.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:18.27,0:11:22.28,Dialogue,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,The implications of what\NJiguro was saying terrified me...
Dialogue: 0,0:11:22.28,0:11:25.48,Dialogue,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,...so I avoided listening to\Nthe rest of their conversation.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:26.32,0:11:30.22,Dialogue,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,After thinking a while, the swordsmith\Nsaid the following to Jiguro.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:30.72,0:11:33.92,Dialogue,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,"In seven days,\Npay me another visit."
Dialogue: 0,0:11:34.62,0:11:38.89,Dialogue,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,The next seven days\Nseemed like an eternity.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:39.13,0:11:43.40,Dialogue,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,For one thing, Jiguro didn't\Neven try to speak to me.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:44.73,0:11:46.84,Dialogue,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,It's finally started\Nto snow out there.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:52.01,0:11:53.28,Dialogue,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Has it, now?
Dialogue: 0,0:11:54.34,0:11:56.55,Dialogue,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,I thought it felt colder.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:56.98,0:11:59.92,Dialogue,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,I'll go make some tea.\NAre those two upstairs?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:11.06,0:12:16.07,Signs,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Moribito Guardian of the Spirit
Dialogue: 0,0:12:24.34,0:12:29.04,Dialogue,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Jiguro, we're already soaked to\Nthe bone. Let's rest here a while!
Dialogue: 0,0:12:29.55,0:12:32.21,Dialogue,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Don't stop! What will\Nwe do if we catch cold?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:32.55,0:12:34.55,Dialogue,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Just keep running until\Nwe reach the city.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:37.69,0:12:38.82,Dialogue,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,What's wrong?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:39.89,0:12:41.06,Dialogue,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Stay here.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:50.50,0:12:51.70,Dialogue,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Well, well.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:52.84,0:12:54.84,Dialogue,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,I knew you would\Nbe the second...
Dialogue: 0,0:13:01.54,0:13:02.51,Dialogue,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Tagul!
Dialogue: 0,0:13:03.28,0:13:05.78,Dialogue,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,I knew that you would come here.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:08.38,0:13:10.39,Dialogue,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,So, what did Logsam tell you?
Dialogue: 0,0:13:10.89,0:13:13.99,Dialogue,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Did he order you to kill the\Nco-conspirators of the physician...
Dialogue: 0,0:13:13.99,0:13:15.22,Dialogue,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,...who poisoned the king?
Dialogue: 0,0:13:20.70,0:13:23.77,Dialogue,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,So, you've taken the\Noath not to hear or speak?
Dialogue: 0,0:13:25.47,0:13:31.17,Dialogue,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,I know better than anyone that\Nyou're a man who dislikes combat.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:32.17,0:13:34.54,Dialogue,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Your wife and children are being\Nheld hostage, aren't they?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:27.76,0:14:28.66,Dialogue,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Tagul!
Dialogue: 0,0:14:30.23,0:14:36.64,Dialogue,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,So you too...have found\Nsomething to protect...at last?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:49.62,0:14:50.72,Dialogue,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Tagul...
Dialogue: 0,0:15:08.10,0:15:11.67,Dialogue,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,When I saw Jiguro\Nbreak down into sobs...
Dialogue: 0,0:15:11.67,0:15:14.11,Dialogue,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,...I didn't know what I should do.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:14.54,0:15:19.25,Dialogue,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,I thought, "This is the only man\NI can turn to. What can I do for him?"
Dialogue: 0,0:15:20.05,0:15:25.09,Dialogue,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,And later on, I learned the\Nreal reason for Jiguro's tears.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:25.95,0:15:28.62,Dialogue,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,The second assassin that\NLogsam had sent after us...
Dialogue: 0,0:15:28.62,0:15:33.13,Dialogue,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,...was Jiguro's closest friend\Namong all the King's Spears.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:33.43,0:15:34.66,Dialogue,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,But, no...
Dialogue: 0,0:15:35.16,0:15:38.70,Dialogue,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Logsam was an\Nutterly fearsome man...
Dialogue: 0,0:15:38.70,0:15:41.97,Dialogue,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,...and he was utterly\Nwithout scruples.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:44.34,0:15:50.25,Dialogue,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,We returned to the Yogo city,\Nand from a Kanbal migrant worker...
Dialogue: 0,0:15:50.25,0:15:53.35,Dialogue,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,...we learned that my\Nfather had been killed.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:56.62,0:16:00.02,Dialogue,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,I had always thought that I would\Nsee my father again someday.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:00.16,0:16:02.76,Dialogue,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,For the first time since\Nwe left Kanbal, I cried.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:03.53,0:16:08.00,Dialogue,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,For someone at my age, that was\Nthe worst possible news I could hear.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:13.84,0:16:16.37,Dialogue,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Jiguro then told me\Neverything that was going on...
Dialogue: 0,0:16:16.37,0:16:19.01,Dialogue,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,...almost as if he were\Nspeaking to an adult.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:20.31,0:16:22.74,Dialogue,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,He explained why my father\Nhad been killed...
Dialogue: 0,0:16:22.74,0:16:26.38,Dialogue,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,...and why I had had to\Nflee the country with him.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:27.68,0:16:31.82,Dialogue,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,The hatred that blossomed\Ninside my heart that day...
Dialogue: 0,0:16:31.82,0:16:35.16,Dialogue,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,...still sits like a lump\Ndeep inside me.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:35.46,0:16:40.40,Dialogue,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,That wish to get my revenge\Nagainst Logsam one day.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:41.80,0:16:46.20,Dialogue,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Sol asked Jiguro to\Nteach me martial arts.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:48.77,0:16:51.81,Dialogue,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Jiguro! Teach me how to fight!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:52.24,0:16:55.78,Dialogue,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,But Jiguro wouldn't\Nagree to my request.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:56.45,0:16:57.38,Dialogue,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,No.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:00.02,0:17:02.08,Dialogue,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,The martial arts\Nare a man's domain.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:02.35,0:17:04.25,Dialogue,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Women's muscles prevent them...
Dialogue: 0,0:17:04.25,0:17:07.29,Dialogue,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,...from making any real headway\Nno matter how hard they try.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:07.86,0:17:10.99,Dialogue,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,And most of all, you're just a child.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:12.33,0:17:16.27,Dialogue,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Even though he'd turned me down\Nso bluntly, I couldn't give up.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:17.57,0:17:21.90,Dialogue,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,From then on, I secretly watched\NJiguro train whenever I got the chance...
Dialogue: 0,0:17:22.14,0:17:25.14,Dialogue,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,...to try to pick up how\Nto use a short spear.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:26.31,0:17:27.64,Dialogue,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Some time after that...
Dialogue: 0,0:17:27.64,0:17:30.25,Dialogue,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,...Jiguro was working as an\Nescort for a merchant caravan.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:30.25,0:17:34.25,Dialogue,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,For us, this killed three\Nbirds with one stone.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:34.72,0:17:39.56,Dialogue,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,The first was that it allowed Jiguro\Nto make a living using his martial arts.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:39.72,0:17:42.52,Dialogue,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,The second was that\NI was continuously...
Dialogue: 0,0:17:42.52,0:17:45.03,Dialogue,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,...able to witness\NJiguro in combat firsthand.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:45.19,0:17:47.96,Dialogue,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,This gave me invaluable\Ninsight into the martial arts.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:48.40,0:17:52.67,Dialogue,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,And the third was that this allowed us\Nto quickly gather information...
Dialogue: 0,0:17:52.67,0:17:55.14,Dialogue,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,...on the people\Nwho were pursuing us.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:55.57,0:17:58.24,Dialogue,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Six people apparently\Nsearching for us?
Dialogue: 0,0:17:58.74,0:18:00.14,Dialogue,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Jiguro, look!
Dialogue: 0,0:18:00.71,0:18:02.21,Dialogue,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,These are your moves, Jiguro!
Dialogue: 0,0:18:07.75,0:18:10.35,Dialogue,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Seeing the amused looks on the\Nfaces of the adults around me...
Dialogue: 0,0:18:10.35,0:18:12.05,Dialogue,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,...caused me to get carried away.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:13.72,0:18:17.59,Dialogue,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,That man went for your\Nspear hand, remember?
Dialogue: 0,0:18:17.86,0:18:21.20,Dialogue,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,And you let go of your spear for a\Nsecond, dodged his strike, and then...
Dialogue: 0,0:18:45.55,0:18:48.39,Dialogue,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Don't ever do that again!\NIs that clear?
Dialogue: 0,0:18:52.39,0:18:54.23,Dialogue,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Why did you do that?
Dialogue: 0,0:18:55.00,0:18:57.53,Dialogue,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Who can say? I'm not really sure.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:58.53,0:19:03.57,Dialogue,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Maybe after seeing the worried\Nlook on his face, I wanted to help.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:03.77,0:19:08.58,Dialogue,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Or maybe I just wanted\Nto get a rise out of him.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:09.08,0:19:12.35,Dialogue,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,After all, that man never\Ntalked to me about anything.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:15.28,0:19:20.39,Dialogue,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,But not long after that, Jiguro\Nbegan to train me in the martial arts.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:21.49,0:19:22.59,Dialogue,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Why?
Dialogue: 0,0:19:22.96,0:19:27.23,Dialogue,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,I think that one reason is that he was\Nimpressed by my little performance.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:28.93,0:19:33.34,Dialogue,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,At the time, I had no idea that\Nwhat I did was extraordinary...
Dialogue: 0,0:19:33.34,0:19:37.31,Dialogue,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,...but apparently, I had\Na gift for the martial arts.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:37.57,0:19:40.98,Dialogue,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,At any rate, I had\Npretty much memorized...
Dialogue: 0,0:19:40.98,0:19:43.91,Dialogue,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,...all of Jiguro's fighting\Nmoves just by watching.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:44.58,0:19:48.28,Dialogue,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,But there was something else.\NOne other reason.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:48.82,0:19:50.52,Dialogue,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Another reason?
Dialogue: 0,0:19:56.86,0:19:58.66,Dialogue,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Starting today, practice with this.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:59.59,0:20:02.56,Dialogue,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,A short spear isn't\Ncreated to fit a body.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:02.90,0:20:05.20,Dialogue,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,You must make\Nyour body fit the spear.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:07.00,0:20:09.20,Dialogue,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Why the change of heart?
Dialogue: 0,0:20:09.64,0:20:15.18,Dialogue,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,I thought you didn't want to force\Nthe girl to live a life of bloodshed.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:18.65,0:20:20.82,Dialogue,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,It's true that for any\Nstudent of the martial arts...
Dialogue: 0,0:20:20.82,0:20:23.02,Dialogue,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,...the more proficient you become...
Dialogue: 0,0:20:23.02,0:20:25.62,Dialogue,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,...the more opponents\Nyou draw to yourself.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:26.02,0:20:31.63,Dialogue,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,As much as I hate to say it,\Nthis path is her only hope of survival.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:33.56,0:20:37.10,Dialogue,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,You've figured that out, have you?
Dialogue: 0,0:20:38.13,0:20:41.44,Dialogue,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Jiguro must have already\Ncaught wind of the rumors...
Dialogue: 0,0:20:41.44,0:20:46.64,Dialogue,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,...that the remaining King's Spears\Nhad joined forces to hunt us down.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:47.38,0:20:50.51,Dialogue,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,And so, he began\Ntraining me in the martial arts...
Dialogue: 0,0:20:50.51,0:20:55.02,Dialogue,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,...so that I would be able to\Nsurvive in the event of his death.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:57.52,0:21:00.99,Dialogue,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Even so, Jiguro\Nwas a cautious man.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:01.62,0:21:05.39,Dialogue,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,He hoped to avoid having to kill\Nany more of his friends if he could...
Dialogue: 0,0:21:05.39,0:21:10.07,Dialogue,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,...so we lived up in Yogo's\Nmountains until our money ran out...
Dialogue: 0,0:21:10.07,0:21:13.37,Dialogue,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,...and didn't take on any\Nhigh-profile bodyguard jobs.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:13.37,0:21:16.47,Dialogue,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Ah, and that's when you met\NTanda and Mistress Torogai.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:16.97,0:21:17.97,Dialogue,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Right.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:18.54,0:21:21.61,Dialogue,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Living that way allowed us\Nto evade the pursuit...
Dialogue: 0,0:21:21.61,0:21:24.31,Dialogue,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,...of the King's Spears\Nfor nearly ten years.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:24.31,0:21:28.95,Dialogue,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Our life was pleasant enough,\Nalthough dangerous.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:33.05,0:21:36.46,Dialogue,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,But then the six\NKing's Spears came, right?
Dialogue: 0,0:21:37.53,0:21:38.39,Dialogue,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Yes.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:40.96,0:21:43.13,Dialogue,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,When a skilled spear-wielder...
Dialogue: 0,0:21:43.13,0:21:47.00,Dialogue,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,...with a young woman in tow\Ntakes on bodyguard jobs...
Dialogue: 0,0:21:47.00,0:21:49.77,Dialogue,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,...word is going to get around\Nwhether you want it to or not.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:51.17,0:21:53.91,Dialogue,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,On the way home after a big job...
Dialogue: 0,0:21:53.91,0:21:56.81,Dialogue,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,...we were finally\Ndiscovered by the King's Spears...
Dialogue: 0,0:21:56.81,0:22:00.08,Dialogue,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,...who had been tracking\Nour activities all that time.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:02.48,0:22:05.89,Dialogue,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Go hide in those rocks over there.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:08.29,0:22:09.26,Dialogue,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Go!
Dialogue: 0,0:22:10.39,0:22:12.33,Dialogue,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,I was reluctant to leave him.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:12.33,0:22:15.70,Dialogue,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,I had believed that I would be\Nable to help Jiguro, at least a little...
Dialogue: 0,0:22:15.70,0:22:18.10,Dialogue,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,...but when the time came\Nto face the King's Spears...
Dialogue: 0,0:22:18.10,0:22:20.07,Dialogue,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,...I wasn't able to do anything.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:20.54,0:22:23.67,Dialogue,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,No, even if I had\Nbeen able to help...
Dialogue: 0,0:22:23.67,0:22:26.34,Dialogue,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,...I'm certain that Jiguro\Nwouldn't have let me.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:27.88,0:22:30.35,Dialogue,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Stop! This will accomplish nothing!
Dialogue: 0,0:22:37.02,0:22:40.26,Dialogue,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Jiguro had already\Nmade up his mind.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:40.69,0:22:43.73,Dialogue,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,He would fight the\NKing's Spears alone.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:44.19,0:22:48.70,Dialogue,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Listen to me! Put away\Nyour spears and return to Kanball
Dialogue: 0,0:22:49.16,0:22:52.17,Dialogue,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,How long do you intend to\Ncontinue such a futile endeavor?
Dialogue: 0,0:22:58.37,0:23:03.01,Dialogue,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Jiguro had decided that\Nhe wouldn't allow my hands...
Dialogue: 0,0:23:03.01,0:23:05.15,Dialogue,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,...to be stained\Nby senseless killing.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:07.72,0:23:13.05,ED,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,As I sat huddled and alone, holding\Nback the tears on those nights...
Dialogue: 0,0:23:13.05,0:23:20.20,ED,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,When it felt like I was about\Nto succumb to my doubts...
Dialogue: 0,0:23:20.20,0:23:25.47,ED,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,...there you were,\Nat my side before I knew it.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:25.47,0:23:32.81,ED,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,It was none other than you\Nwho was there for me.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:32.81,0:23:47.09,ED,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,I keep wishing, "I want to be strong."\NI stumble and hurt myself again.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:47.09,0:23:56.46,ED,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,But because I have you to believe in,\NI can get back to my feet.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:56.46,0:24:03.24,ED,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,I simply want to tell\Nmy dear one, "Thank you. "
Dialogue: 0,0:24:03.24,0:24:08.38,ED,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,At the top of my lungs,\Nagain and again.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:08.38,0:24:16.75,ED,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,I call out to my precious loved one.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:16.75,0:24:20.96,ED,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Is my voice reaching you?
Dialogue: 0,0:24:20.96,0:24:29.20,ED,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,In this world that always changes,\Nhuman warmth never does.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:29.20,0:24:39.51,ED,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,I'm certain I sensed the presence\Nof the one that I hold dear.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:42.01,0:24:44.78,Signs,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Next Time
Dialogue: 0,0:24:42.84,0:24:46.01,Dialogue,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,From Jiguro to Balsa.\NFrom Balsa to Chagum.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:46.75,0:24:50.22,Dialogue,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Inherited desires. Tested bonds.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:51.25,0:24:53.49,Dialogue,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Next time, "Season of Awakening."
Dialogue: 0,0:24:52.02,0:24:57.03,Signs,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Episode 22\NSeason of Awakening
Dialogue: 0,0:24:54.12,0:24:57.03,Dialogue,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Spring is almost upon us.
